Eden recommended that she consult <a0_0>Lord Salisbury<a0_0/>, the <a1_0><b8_0>Lord President of the Council<b8_0/><a1_0/>. Lord Salisbury and Lord Kilmuir, the <a3_0>Lord Chancellor<a3_0/>, consulted the <a4_0>British Cabinet<a4_0/>, Winston Churchill, and the Chairman of the backbench <b5_0><b6_0><b7_0><b9_0>1922<b9_0/><b7_0/><b6_0/><b5_0/> Committee, resulting in the Queen appointing their recommended candidate: <a2_0>Harold Macmillan<a2_0/>.
